<br>
I started my Epic in May 2002, and so far I have the Golem and VS – all I need is the Blue Crystal Staff from Phinny.<br>
<br>
Two things are worrying me though. Firstly, when I con Solomen he’s apprehensive to me, but he does talk to me without a problem. I’ve heard that to be *safe* with the final turn-in you need to be indifferent. The Gnome in Butcherblock conned apprehensive to me too, but he *did* give me the staff and the note.<br>
<br>
As I’m worried about my faction, I had a couple of friends come with me to Butcherblock Mountains. A Druid killed Pegleg for me, and as the Lesser Spirit wouldn’t give me the time of day my Enchantress friend charmed it. I then managed to get the tiny gem and proceeded to Freeport to give this to the Barbarian guy.<br>
<br>
The guy in Freeport doesn’t much care for me either, though I'm not KoS to him, so he was charmed and I handed him the gem – I was awarded experience but interestingly enough I was given *no* faction increase of any kind. Can someone please tell me why this might be – perhaps I did something wrong?<br>
<br>
I’ve met someone that is actually trying to sell a MQ of the Blue Crystal Staff – whilst my initial reaction was to be filled with joy at the prospect of completing my Epic my happiness was soon to be shattered when I saw that he was a Dark Elf Necromancer. His TrueSpirit faction is bound to be messed up, so I’m *very* reluctant to risk my two items. Someone has suggested that the Necro might be able to have an illusion cast upon him – can anyone please give me some advice as to firstly, up my TrueSpirit faction, and secondly, how (if at all) I can MQ the staff with a Necro.<br>
<br>
Many thanks in advance.<br>
