<br>
Go to Butcherblock with an Enchanter and kill Pegleg.  That will spawn &quot;a lesser spirit&quot; - it's part of the Shaman epic.  Have the enchanter charm the lesser spirit, and then say the key phrase (which I think is &quot;I wish to know more&quot;).  You will get a lore no drop gem.<br>
<br>
Go to North Freeport and find Bondl (I think that's his name) in the sewer.  He's a drunken barbarian.  Using the invis trick (put the gem up in the trade window, have someone invis you, then hit trade/give), hand Bondl the gem.  You can not charm him, or else you will not get the faction hit when you hand in the gem.<br>
<br>
Then head back to Butcherblock and repeat until you are indifferent.  You can also do this with the lesser spirit in EJ, or OOT, but the Butcherblock one is the most convenient.<br>
<br>
You don't need to worry about keeping the lesser spirit around during turn-ins.  The lesser spirit will stay up for about 7.5 minutes and - how convenient - the spawn time on Pegleg is about 7.5 minutes.  If the spirit isn't up when you get back, just kill Pegleg again.  He will be up.<br>
<br>
Using this method (which isn't the quickest method, but only uses a Wiz and Chanter, as opposed to a Wiz, Chanter, and Dru), of charming the spirit, then porting my Chanter friend and I to N Ro and running to NFP for the trade, I got from apprehensive to indifferent in just over an hour.<br>
<br>
Note that once you are indifferent, you don't need the Chanter to charm the lesser spirit or to invis you for the gem trade.  So for those of you wanting to get to amiable (for no good reason really, but hey, I did it), you can do it solo once you get to indiff.<br>
<br>
And again, some info on this may be inaccurate/incomplete.  For those who have done it more recently and remember it better, please correct.<br>
<br>
